'''August William Kuchler''' (born ''August Wilhelm Küchler''; 1907–1999) was a German-born [[United States|American]] [[geographer]] and naturalist who is noted for developing a [[Phytocoenosis|plant association]] system in widespread use in the United States.<ref>A. Watkins</ref> Some of this database has become digitized for integration into [[GIS]] mapping systems.<ref>A. W. Kuchler, 1996</ref> Kuchler received his Ph.D. in geography from [[University of Munich]] in 1935.<ref>[http://www.aag.org/cs/honors Honors of the Association of American Geographers]</ref> In 1978, he received the [[Association of American Geographers]]' Honors award.<ref>[http://www.aag.org/cs/honors Honors of the Association of American Geographers]</ref> He is the publisher of the book ''Vegetation Mapping'' <ref>[http://www.aag.org/cs/honors Honors of the Association of American Geographers]</ref>

