'''Title 10 of the Code of Federal Regulations''' is one of fifty titles comprising the United States [[Code of Federal Regulations]] (CFR), containing the principal set of rules and regulations issued by federal agencies regarding nuclear energy. It is available in digital and printed form, and can be referenced online using the [http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/ECFR?page=browse Electronic Code of Federal Regulations] (e-CFR).
== Structure ==
The table of contents, as reflected in the e-CFR updated June 19, 2014, is as follows:<ref name="10 CFR Table of Contents">[http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=5e72713084a99117835b0439039ab3c6&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title10/10tab_02.tpl], Retrieved 20 June 2014.</ref>
{| class="wikitable" |- ! Volume !! Chapter !! Parts !! Regulatory Entity |- | 1 || rowspan="2" | I || [http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi/t/text/text-idx?SID=5e72713084a99117835b0439039ab3c6&c=ecfr&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title10/10cfrv1_02.tpl 0-50] || rowspan="2" | [[Nuclear Regulatory Commission]] |- | 2 || [http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi/t/text/text-idx?SID=5e72713084a99117835b0439039ab3c6&c=ecfr&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title10/10cfrv2_02.tpl 51-199] |- | 3 || rowspan="2" | II || [http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi/t/text/text-idx?SID=5e72713084a99117835b0439039ab3c6&c=ecfr&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title10/10cfrv3_02.tpl 200-499] || rowspan="2" | [[United States Department of Energy|Department of Energy]] |- | rowspan="6" | 4 || [http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi/t/text/text-idx?SID=5e72713084a99117835b0439039ab3c6&c=ecfr&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title10/10cfrv4_02.tpl 500-699] |- | III || [http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi/t/text/text-idx?SID=5e72713084a99117835b0439039ab3c6&c=ecfr&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title10/10cfrv4_02.tpl#700 700-999] || Department of Energy |- | X || [http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi/t/text/text-idx?SID=5e72713084a99117835b0439039ab3c6&c=ecfr&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title10/10cfrv4_02.tpl#1000 1000-1099] || Department of Energy (General Provisions) |- | XIII || [http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi/t/text/text-idx?SID=5e72713084a99117835b0439039ab3c6&c=ecfr&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title10/10cfrv4_02.tpl#1300 1300-1399] || [[Nuclear Waste Technical Review Board]] |- | XVII || [http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi/t/text/text-idx?SID=5e72713084a99117835b0439039ab3c6&c=ecfr&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title10/10cfrv4_02.tpl#1700 1700-1799] || [[Defense Nuclear Facilities Safety Board]] |- | XVIII || [http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi/t/text/text-idx?SID=5e72713084a99117835b0439039ab3c6&c=ecfr&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title10/10cfrv4_02.tpl#1800 1800-1899] || [[Northeast Interstate Low-Level Radioactive Waste Commission]] |}
Parts 0 to 199 are the requirements (and reserved for the requirements) prescribed by the United States [[Nuclear Regulatory Commission]] (NRC) and binding on all persons and organizations who receive a license from NRC to use nuclear materials or operate nuclear facilities. Licensing is required for the design, manufacture, construction, operation and decommissioning of [[nuclear reactor]]s. These facilities can be commercial, research or test reactors. The authority is broad covering the licensing of individual facilitatory operators to the entities which operate these facilities.
